Observing and analyzing the work of a speech therapist with patient with acquired neurogenic communication disorder. Practical exercises in aphasia and motor speech disorders. Self-analysis, reflection.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the practicum is to apply the theoretical knowledge gained during aphasia and speech motor disorders courses during practical exercises/activities.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1.	Student has primary skills for assessing adults speech, language and communication skills, diagnosing acquired speech/language/communication disorders 
2.	Student has primary skills for planning therapy for patients with acquired neurogenic communication disorders and assessing its effectiveness. 
3.	Student has an idea about treatment of neurological patients in Estonia 
4.	Student orients in patient`s medical history, finds useful information for speech therapy
5.	Studeng is able to write a summary of patient with acquired neurological communication disorder suitable for medical history under guidance
